author: COMSOL
description: This example computes the flow between two sealed chambers connected by a microchannel with conducting walls when the chambers are maintained at different temperatures. No net flow occurs down the duct, but a pressure gradient and a circulating flow develops. This is a benchmark problem for the slip flow interface.
label: slip_flow_benchmark.mph
